cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about developing a new framework for deep neural networks for image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the proposed framework, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves decision policy learning, which is a subfield of reinforcement learning, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the structure of the neural network, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves experimental results on image datasets, which could suggest that it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia).
